# Sūra XXVI.: Shu‘arāa, or The Poets.

### Section 5

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_070.gif)

70. I<u>th</u> q<u>a</u>la li-abeehi waqawmihi m<u>a</u> taAAbudoon**a**

70\. And rehearse to them  
(Something of) Abraham's story.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_071.gif)

71. Q<u>a</u>loo naAAbudu a<u>s</u>n<u>a</u>man fana*<u>th</u>*allu
lah<u>a</u> AA<u>a</u>kifeen**a**

71\. Behold, he said  
To his father and his people:  
"What worship ye?"

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_072.gif)

72. Q<u>a</u>la hal yasmaAAoonakum i<u>th</u> tadAAoon**a**

72\. They said: "We worship  
Idols, and we remain constantly  
In attendance on them."

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_073.gif)

73. Aw yanfaAAoonakum aw ya<u>d</u>urroon**a**

73\. He said: "Do they listen  
To you when ye call (on them),  
Or do you good or harm?"

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_074.gif)

74. Q<u>a</u>loo bal wajadn<u>a</u> <u>a</u>b<u>a</u>an<u>a</u>
ka<u>tha</u>lika yafAAaloon**a**

74\. They said: "Nay, but we  
Found our fathers doing  
Thus (what we do)."

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_075.gif)

75. Q<u>a</u>la afaraaytum m<u>a</u> kuntum taAAbudoon**a**

75\. He said: "Do ye then  
See whom ye have been  
Worshipping,—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_076.gif)

76. Antum wa<u>a</u>b<u>a</u>okumu al-aqdamoon**a**

76\. "Ye and your fathers before you?—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_077.gif)

77. Fa-innahum AAaduwwun lee ill<u>a</u> rabba alAA<u>a</u>lameen**a**

77\. "For they are enemies to me;  
Not so the Lord and Cherisher  
Of the Worlds;

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_078.gif)

78. Alla<u>th</u>ee khalaqanee fahuwa yahdeen**i**

78\. "Who created me, and  
It is He who guides me;

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_079.gif)

79. Wa**a**lla<u>th</u>ee huwa yu<u>t</u>AAimunee wayasqeen**i**

79\. "Who gives me food and drink,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_080.gif)

80. Wa-i<u>tha</u> mari<u>d</u>tu fahuwa yashfeen**i**

80\. "And when I am ill,  
It is He who cures me;

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_081.gif)

81. Wa**a**lla<u>th</u>ee yumeetunee thumma yu<u>h</u>yeen**i**

81\. "Who will cause me to die,  
And then to live (again);

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_082.gif)

82. Wa**a**lla<u>th</u>ee a<u>t</u>maAAu an yaghfira lee
kha<u>t</u>ee-atee yawma a**l**ddeen**i**

82\. "And who, I hope,  
Will forgive me my faults  
On the Day of Judgment.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_083.gif)

83. Rabbi hab lee <u>h</u>ukman waal<u>h</u>iqnee
bi**al**<u>ssa</u>li<u>h</u>een**a**

83\. "O my Lord! bestow wisdom  
On me, and join me  
With the righteous;

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_084.gif)

84. Wa**i**jAAal lee lis<u>a</u>na <u>s</u>idqin fee
al-<u>a</u>khireen**a**

84\. "Grant me honourable mention  
On the tongue of truth  
Among the latest (generations);

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_085.gif)

85. Wa**i**jAAalnee min warathati jannati a**l**nnaAAeem**i**

85\. "Make me one of the inheritors  
Of the Garden of Bliss;

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_086.gif)

86. Wa**i**ghfir li-abee innahu k<u>a</u>na mina
a**l**<u>dda</u>lleen**a**

86\. "Forgive my father, for that  
He is among those astray;

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_087.gif)

87. Wal<u>a</u> tukhzinee yawma yubAAathoon**a**

87\. "And let me not be  
In disgrace on the Day  
When (men) will be raised up;—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_088.gif)

88. Yawma l<u>a</u> yanfaAAu m<u>a</u>lun wal<u>a</u> banoon**a**

88\. "The Day whereon neither  
Wealth nor sons will avail,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_089.gif)

89. Ill<u>a</u> man at<u>a</u> All<u>a</u>ha biqalbin saleem**in**

89\. "But only he (will prosper)  
That brings to God  
A sound heart;

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_090.gif)

90. Waozlifati aljannatu lilmuttaqeen**a**

90\. "To the righteous, the Garden  
Will be brought near,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_091.gif)

91. Waburrizati alja<u>h</u>eemu lilgh<u>a</u>ween**a**

91\. "And to those straying in Evil,  
The Fire will be placed  
In full view;

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_092.gif)

92. Waqeela lahum ayna m<u>a</u> kuntum taAAbudoon**a**

92\. "And it shall be said  
To them, 'Where are  
The (gods) ye worshipped—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_093.gif)

93. Min dooni All<u>a</u>hi hal yan<u>s</u>uroonakum aw
yanta<u>s</u>iroon**a**

93\. "'Besides God? Can they  
Help you or help themselves?'

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_094.gif)

94. Fakubkiboo feeh<u>a</u> hum wa**a**lgh<u>a</u>woon**a**

94\. "Then they will be thrown  
Headlong into the (Fire),—  
They and those straying  
In Evil,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_095.gif)

95. Wajunoodu ibleesa ajmaAAoon**a**

95\. "And the whole hosts  
Of Iblīs together.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_096.gif)

96. Q<u>a</u>loo wahum feeh<u>a</u> yakhta<u>s</u>imoon**a**

96\. "They will say there  
In their mutual bickerings:

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_097.gif)

97. Ta**A**ll<u>a</u>hi in kunn<u>a</u> lafee <u>d</u>al<u>a</u>lin
mubeen**in**

97\. "'By God, we were truly  
In an error manifest,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_098.gif)

98. I<u>th</u> nusawweekum birabbi alAA<u>a</u>lameen**a**

98\. "'When we held you as equals  
With the Lord of the Worlds;

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_099.gif)

99. Wam<u>a</u> a<u>d</u>allan<u>a</u> ill<u>a</u> almujrimoon**a**

99\. "'And our seducers were  
Only those who were  
Steeped in guilt.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_100.gif)

100. Fam<u>a</u> lan<u>a</u> min sh<u>a</u>fiAAeen**a**

100\. "'Now, then, we have none  
To intercede (for us),

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_101.gif)

101. Wal<u>a</u> <u>s</u>adeeqin <u>h</u>ameem**in**

101\. "'Nor a single friend  
To feel (for us).

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_102.gif)

102. Falaw anna lan<u>a</u> karratan fanakoona mina almu/mineen**a**

102\. "'Now if we only had  
A chance of return,  
We shall truly be  
Of those who believe!'"

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_103.gif)

103. Inna fee <u>tha</u>lika la<u>a</u>yatan wam<u>a</u> k<u>a</u>na
aktharuhum mu/mineen**a**

103\. Verily in this is a Sign  
But most of them  
Do not believe.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/026/026_104.gif)

104. Wa-inna rabbaka lahuwa alAAazeezu a**l**rra<u>h</u>eem**u**

104\. And verily thy Lord  
Is He, the Exalted in Might,  
Most Merciful.

